{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":328,"record_hash":"sha256:ee1051e6e5a2cfd53e35c883557eac8173d6b50ac9253d416c323906c3b63309","timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:01:45.058Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"<proposed_plan>\n# Agent Session Capture POC Implementation Plan\n\n## Summary\nImplement the first Codex-only capture POC described in [First POC Implementation Contract]([REDACTED:entropy].md:1), with broader behavior referenced from [Architecture](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/agent-session-capture/architecture.md:1), [Capture Workflow]([REDACTED:entropy].md:1), and [GitMeta Data Model]([REDACTED:entropy].md:1).\n\nThe POC adds a new `but-capture` Rust crate and a hidden, feature-gated CLI command:\n\n```text\nbut agent-session capture --agent codex --transcript-path <path> [--target project] [--include-transcript] [--dry-run]\n```\n\nUse the pinned GitMeta dependency already recorded in the docs:\n\n```toml\ngit-meta-lib = { git = \"https://github.com/git-meta/git-meta.git\", rev = \"[REDACTED:entropy]\" }\n```\n\n## Key Changes\n- Add `crates/but-capture` as the owner of capture behavior, with no dependency on `but-api`, `but-db`, `but-ctx`, `but-claude`, `but-cursor`, or legacy virtual branch APIs.\n- Add `capture = [\"dep:but-capture\"]` to the `but` CLI crate and compile the hidden `agent-session capture` command only with that feature.\n- CLI repository resolution uses `gix::discover(&args.current_dir)` and passes the canonical worktree root to `but-capture`; bare repositories fail clearly.\n- `CaptureRequest` includes repo path, agent string, transcript path, optional target string, `include_transcript`, and `dry_run`.\n- `CaptureReport` is `serde::Serialize` with camelCase JSON fields matching the contract, including basename-only transcript reporting.\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Parse only Codex JSONL from an explicit transcript path. Empty lines are ignored. Record indexes are 0-based over non-empty physical JSONL records.\n- Read the transcript into one byte snapshot before parsing. Hash the whole snapshot for `source-sha256` and each trimmed raw record as `sha256:<hex>`.\n- Tolerate one malformed final non-empty line as a partial write and skip it. Any malformed earlier line fails. Errors and reports must not include full transcript paths.\n- Extract best-effort Codex fields from `session_meta`, `turn_context`, `response_item`, and `event_msg`; preserve the full parsed source record in transcript envelopes.\n- Validate any transcript `cwd` by canonicalizing it and requiring it to be the repo root or inside the repo worktree. Missing `cwd` is allowed.\n- Store POC data only under `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:<agent>:<session-key>:*`. Do not write publishable `agent:*` keys in this POC.\n- Use safe session keys: raw session id when it is a valid key segment, otherwise `sha256-<prefix>` from the raw session id; if missing, hash the canonical source path.\n- Read `seen-record-hashes` and `transcript-record-hashes` via `handle.get_value()` and `MetaValue::Set`; missing keys mean empty sets, wrong value types fail.\n- Keep metadata dedupe and transcript dedupe separate, so a metadata-only run followed by `--include-transcript` appends envelopes exactly once.\n- `--dry-run` reads and plans against existing GitMeta state but performs no writes.\n- `bytesCaptured` is the sum of trimmed raw JSONL bytes for records that cause a new metadata hash or a new transcript envelope in that run, counted once per record.\n- Human and shell output use the exact contract phrases. JSON output uses `OutputChannel::write_value(&report)`.\n\n## Tests\n- `cargo test -p but-capture` covers Codex parsing, field extraction, partial-final-line handling, malformed-middle-line failure, cwd mismatch, unsafe session keys, target defaulting, dry-run no writes, and idempotency.\n- GitMeta integration tests create a temp Git repo, configure `user.name` and `user.email`, run capture, then inspect GitMeta values via `git-meta-lib`.\n- Dedupe tests cover first capture `N`, second capture `0`, fixture growth, metadata-only then transcript backfill, and separate hash sets.\n- CLI tests with `--features capture` cover hidden command parsing, unsupported agent failure, required transcript path, terse human output, JSON output, and no full transcript path leakage.\n- Validation commands: `cargo fmt`, `cargo test -p but-capture`, and `cargo check -p but --features capture`.\n\n## Assumptions\n- The implementation contract wins over broader docs where they differ.\n- Only `codex` is supported. No Claude, Cursor, session discovery, `CODEX_THREAD_ID`, background watcher, branch inference, commit inference, UI, GitMeta sync, push, fetch, or serialization.\n- `--target` defaults to `project`; other explicit target strings are passed directly to `git_meta_lib::Target::parse` without custom inference.\n- Transcript envelopes use a fixed JSON shape with unknown optional fields serialized as `null`.\n</proposed_plan>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:01:45.058Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}